 Core responsibilities include:
 Fulfills the functions of an Agile Junior Scrum Master who is filling in gaps with all the other scrum masters.
 Coordinates with Scrum Masters and conducts Scrum on Scrum.
 Building high-performing Agile teams
 Look for ways to strengthen teams understanding of Agile / Scrum concepts and principles
 Ensure Scrum practices are used and improved within and across teams
 Bring transparency to Business and IT organization about development and grow trust
 Foster a continuous learning environment helping teams to inspect & adapt
 Leverages Jira and Confluence to elicit and define business and technical requirements, track requirements, prioritize features, curate content, sequence deliverables into sprints, and report progress
 Leads Increment and sprint planning sessions and documents resulting story boards
 Facilitates the daily scrum meeting and supports delivery teams (pods) in execution of scrum methodology
 Responsible for maintenance and tracking of sprint backlog and prioritization
 Documents and leads remediation / removal of blockers during sprints
 Collaborates with the Agile coach to maintain accountability and compliance with the defined Agile delivery methodology
 Ensures that teams actions are aligned with Epics, Features and Stories
 Responsible to Monitor, Measure, & Report Progress of the team including burndown charts, team velocity
 Ensure good relationship between the team and product owner as well as others outside the team
 Good problem-solving, organizational and analytical skills, with the ability to coach and mentor all roles on a scrum team
 Inspire people to deliver key results, demonstrate the passion for the business
 Required skills:
 Strong communications and interpersonal skills; demonstrated ability to quickly build trust and relationships, manage matrixed teams, bridge communication gaps, resolve conflicts, and influence stakeholders
 Strong technical aptitude and ability to quickly learn new products, lines of business, processes, software, systems, and client needs
 Closely works other scrum masters to gain consensus, and cooperation in the face of conflicting viewpoints, understand to change, constraints, etc.
 Good at building relationships and navigating through organizations.
 Able to develop and foster collaborative teamwork and facilitate team dynamics
